 Class is limited to 16 students; cost is $55/student.

 In order to obtain your concealed handgun license (CHL) in Texas, you must take a class consisting of 4-6 hours of classroom instruction, a multiple choice exam, and a live fire demonstration. If the thought of sitting in a classroom for 4-6 hours of state mandated training reminds you of everything that’s wrong with defensive driving classes, you’ve come to the right place. Texas CHL classes from Hooten Armory are fun. The instructor is passionate about firearms, safety and proficiency. Our training philosophy is that if you are enjoying yourself, you will absorb more information, you’ll retain it longer, and you’ll be more willing to continue your education. As the saying goes, time really does fly when you are having fun.

 The course begins in the classroom and covers four topics: Handgun Use, Safe and Proper Storage of Handguns and Ammunition, Non-Violent Dispute Resolution, and the legal Use of Force. This is followed by a 25 question multiple choice exam. We will then break for lunch and meet at the range for the firearms proficiency demonstration. 

 Class will start at 8:00 AM and we should wrap up around 2-2:30 PM.

title: For Sale:  1996 Jeep Cherokee 4.0 5 Speed, 4wd, heavily modified
postcontent:
I decided to sell my 1996 Jeep Cherokee. I have done extensive modifications and maintenance on this vehicle. I am selling it due to the fact that I would like something newer, and as a 2nd vehicle is no longer needed. It currently has 192k on it, will go up since it is a daily driver. It has the the straight 6, 4.0 liter engine coupled with the AX-15 5 Speed manual transmission. It has a working 4wd system that is amazing in the snow and poor weather. I originally bought this vehicle in 2014 to use as a poor weather vehicle when my other vehicle was stored. After getting into the off-road scene and seeing how expensive and time consuming it is, along with my multiple other hobbies. It was not feasible to have multiple very expensive hobbies. This vehicle has only been to the badlands once and seen mud deeper than 6 inches a hand full of times. It has never left me stranded and is in 100% perfect mechanical order. I am a Master ASE Technician at my full time job and take care of every one of my vehicles to the fullest extent. Here is the (very) long list of recent upgrades and maintenance items.

Now with a vehicle that is almost 20 years old there are some known issues that I will list here.

Other parts include, stainless steel rear extended brake line, spare ujoint, other misc. parts that I will 
include with the vehicle purchase. I have well over $6k in receipts not including my labor. This vehicle is far from perfect but I made it as perfect as I can with what time and money I have put into it. I would have no problem getting into it and driving for another 100k miles. There are some issues with the vehicle but nothing to hinder you from daily driving it. Don't expect a perfect vehicle.

title: For Sale:  Saiga 12 with 6 drums. Converted-mostly done
postcontent:
I bought this with the intent of using it in 3 gun and It still sits as I got it and can keep sitting so please no lowball offers.

So we have a saiga 12..converted trigger and parts which are all US 922 compliant. A barrel shroud with teeth on the end which looks nice. A usa made quardrail. Notched safety so you can lock the bolt back. 5- 12 round drums (over $350) that run perfectly. Weapon functions great on any shell 1300fps or faster including bird shot. Example I used Estate brand cheap birdshot at 1300 fps and never had a jam. Use the super cheap shit at 1000 or 1100 fps and expect 10 to 15% FTE's. With OO buck I would not hesitate to use for home defense...she will fire.

The bad: it's not terrible. The buttstock needs replaced. Screw hole is stripped in stock. Gun is fine. I placed a couple drops of gorilla glue just to hold screw in. Easily replaced. Federal XM855 5.56 NATO with the 62 grain SS109 projectile commonly referred to as "green tip". This is the Light Armor Piercing (LAP) ammunition that the ATF has proposed to ban from further importation and distribution. This ammunition has not yet been banned, but it is already increasing in value and getting hard to find. postcontent: Sealed case - 500 rounds of German surplus ammo. These are the famous blue plastic bullets designed for use in the HK91 assault rifle when used with the practice bolt. They shoot great in traditional bolt actions, too. Experience all the bang and flash of a regular 7.62x51 round, but ZERO RECOIL. I've used these quite a bit in indoor ranges, and your paper target doesn't know the difference between the plastic bullet and a standard metal one.
